"n.表面磨损 【英】 表面磨损(scraping or rubbing off, as of skin) 【考】 scuff : abrasion / heat : vaporization(使磨损导致磨损/加 热导致蒸发) n. 磨损; (皮肤上的)擦伤处 【例】abrasion resistance 抗磨性 wind abrasion 风化 【类】scuff: abrasion = heat: vaporization 使磨损导致磨损 = 加热导致蒸发lubricate: abrasion = seal: leakage 润滑阻止磨损 = 密封阻止泄漏 无 abrasion (n.)  1650s, from Medieval Latin abrasionem (nominative abrasio) ""a scraping,"" noun of action from past participle stem of Latin abradere ""to scrape away, shave off,"" from ab- ""off"" (see ab-) + radere ""to scrape"" (see raze)."
